{
  "texts": [
    "Our study has certain limitations.",
    "Within the PRISMA framework, potential biases may arise from the selection of literature from a specific database.",
    "With respect to BERT topic modeling, we recognize its strength in handling large datasets and uncovering key themes by extracting coherent topic representations on the basis of the semantic similarity of words and phrases.",
    "This reduces human biases in topic classification, thereby enhancing the objectivity and reliability of the findings (Kimura, 2024).",
    "However, the effectiveness of topic modeling algorithms can be influenced by the quality of the input data and the assumptions embedded in their design."
  ]
}